      <scopecontent id="aspace_90f46f03781b2a7db00604452d8fb915">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of six titles from the University Outline series with accompanying material, including a newsclipping and a legal opinion concerning the copyright issues surrounding the series. The outlines are based on Yale courses in American literature, geology, French, and psychology. The materials were compiled by William W. Crawford (Yale 1938). Included are notices of loans awarded to Crawford by the Yale Bureau of Appointments.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
